An enterprise has a Snowflake organization with accounts named MYORG.PROD, MYORG.DEV, and MYORG.ANALYTICS. A developer connects to MYORG.DEV and runs the following:

USE ROLE ORGADMIN;
SHOW ACCOUNTS;

The output shows only one account. Why?

A data provider has the following share structure:

CREATE SHARE sales_share;
GRANT USAGE ON DATABASE sales_db TO SHARE sales_share;
GRANT USAGE ON SCHEMA sales_db.public TO SHARE sales_share;
GRANT SELECT ON VIEW sales_db.public.customer_summary TO SHARE sales_share;

The VIEW customer_summary joins CUSTOMERS and ORDERS tables. Later, the provider tries to also share the underlying CUSTOMERS table and gets an error. What is the most likely cause?
